 ### 9. Optional – Deploy to Toolforge

 If you later want to host the tool on Toolforge (the official hosting for Wikimedia tools):

 1. Create the tool (run on your local machine):

    ```bash
      ssh login.toolforge.org
      toolforge tools create wikipano
      webservice --backend=kubernetes node start
    ```

 2. Deploy the prototype (run from your local machine):

    ```bash
      rsync -avz --exclude='node_modules' --exclude='cache' --exclude='images' \
           prototype/ alih@login.toolforge.org:/data/project/wikipano/www/
    ```

 3. The tour_server.mjs file is already the entry point, so no code changes are required.

 4. The {{PanoTour}} template you just created will automatically link to the new tool.

